(1, 'About Us2', 'about-us', '', '<p><strong>ABOUT US2</strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #545151; font-family: arial; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>An engineering cell of early 1960s</strong></span> having an Engineering Advisor as a team leader and one Executive Engineer with a very few number of supporting staff, has now expanded as Education Engineering Department with a total manpower of 1218 nos. </span><br style="color: #545151; font-family: arial; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;" /><br style="color: #545151; font-family: arial; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;" /><span style="color: #545151; font-family: arial; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;">As a single government department in educational buildings construction sector, Education Engineering Department is involved in Planning, Designing, Monitoring and Reporting of development works in Rural, Urban and Semi-urban areas, Construction/Reconstruction Development of Class Rooms, Laboratories, Libraries, Hostels, Repair and Renovation of Government and<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong> Non-Government Secondary Schools</strong></span>, Colleges, Teacher''s Training Colleges, Vocational Training Institutes, Polytechnic Institutes, College of Leather Technology, College of Textile Technology, Engineering Universities, National University, Text Book Board, Secondary and Higher Education Board etc. including supply of furniture. Besides, the Education Engineering Department is also involved in implementing special projects on turnkey basis such as construction of 14 storied building of National University at Gazipur, Kabi Nazrul University at Trisal, Mymensingh Projects of University Grant Commission like Comilla University etc. The success of Education Engineering Department is noteworthy and has set up an example in serving the national not only for construction/re-construction, repair and renovation and supply of furniture to educational institutions but also for the development of human resources.</span></p>\r\n<p style="color: #545151; font-family: arial; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;">The Head Quarter of Education Engineering Department is situated at Shikkha Bhaban, Abdul Gani Road, Dhaka with one Chief Engineer, two Superintending Engineer and five nos. of Executive Engineers with a good number of supporting staff. There are 34-Zonal offices headed by 34-Executive Engineers, 1-Assistant Engineer at District level and 1-Sub-Assistant Engineer at each Upazilla with supporting staff.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #545151; font-family: arial; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;">Despite achieving success in implementation of the govt. policy regarding development of educational infrastructure the Education Engineering Department has long been suffering from the shortage of required number of personnel and lack of necessary logistic to carry forward its broadbased activities effectively around the country.</p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #545151; font-family: arial; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;">We urge the government to look these problems and to take appropriate steps soon so that the Education Engineering Department can overcome all of its organisational impediments and can be able to implement the development activities speedily bringing revolution in constructing academic buildings throughout the country.</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', -2, 0, 0, 0, '2012-07-14 04:50:14', 62, '', '2013-01-05 17:13:39', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-07-14 04:50:14', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 433, 'robots=\nauthor='),
