(25, 'History of EED', 'history-of-eed', '', '<p>As a single government department in  educational buildings  construction sector, Education Engineering Department is  involved in  Planning, Designing, Monitoring and Reporting of development works  in  Rural, Urban and Semi-urban areas, Construction/Reconstruction  Development  of Class Rooms, Laboratories, Libraries, Hostels, Repair  and Renovation of  Government and Non-Government Secondary Schools,  Colleges, Teachersâ€™ Training  Colleges, Vocational Training Institutes,  Polytechnic Institutes, College of  Leather Technology, College of  Textile Technology, Engineering Universities,  National University, Text  Book Board, Secondary and Higher Education Board etc.  including supply  of furniture. Besides, the Education Engineering Department is  also  involved in implementing special projects on turnkey basis such as   construction of 14 storied building of National University at Gazipur,  Kabi  Nazrul University at Trisal, Mymensingh Projects of University  Grant Commission  like Comilla University etc. The success of Education  Engineering Department is  noteworthy and has set up an example in  serving the national not only for  construction/re-construction, repair  and renovation and supply of furniture to  educational institutions but  also for the development of human resources.</p>\r\n<p>The Head Quarter of Education  Engineering Department  is situated at Shikkha Bhaban, Abdul Gani Road, Dhaka  with one Chief  Engineer, two Superintending Engineer and five nos. of Executive   Engineers with a good number of supporting staff. There are 34-Zonal  offices  headed by 34-Executive Engineers, 1-Assistant Engineer at  District level and  1-Sub-Assistant Engineer at each Upazilla with  supporting staff.</p>\r\n<p>Despite achieving success in  implementation of the govt.  policy regarding development of educational  infrastructure the  Education Engineering Department has long been suffering  from the  shortage of required number of personnel and lack of necessary  logistic  to carry forward its broadbased activities effectively around the   country.</p>\r\n<p>We urge the  government to look these problems and to take  appropriate steps soon so that  the Education Engineering Department can  overcome all of its organisational  impediments and can be able to  implement the development activities speedily  bringing revolution in  constructing academic buildings throughout the country.</p>', '', -2, 0, 0, 0, '2012-07-29 20:01:35', 62, '', '2012-09-13 02:26:04', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-07-29 20:01:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 4, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 138, 'robots=\nauthor='),
